FBIS3-52177 "drnes001_n_94003" FBIS-NES-94-001 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Jan 1994 LEBANON Al-Murr: Al-Asad-Clinton Meeting `Watershed' NC0201175094 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1630 GMT 2 Jan 94 NC0201175094 Beirut Radio Lebanon Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] Deputy Prime Minister Michel al-Murr has affirmed that the region will embark on a qualitative change in the course toward peace in the next two months. He has also indicated the al-Asad-Clinton meeting in the middle of the month will be an important watershed for the course toward peace and a new turning point for all the crises that we have encountered. Al-Murr denied that there are any differences among government members. He indicated that the government encourages Lebanese to invest their funds in Lebanon. [passage omitted]
